name: Adder Canyon
description:
Introduction

Three free-hanging rappels in rapid fire succession followed by a short down-climbing section to the top of a 400 foot slab and finishing with a seasonal water slide, combined with soaring views of the valley below with the Bookcliffs as the backdrop make for a rewarding and relaxing half-day trip. On the first descent we used retrievable anchors on the last two rappels. NOTE: the penultimate rappel can be done with a 200 foot rope if you bring webbing to sling the tree and extend the webbing 10 feet. If you are doing a retrievable you will need a 220 foot rope. Bring a carpet sample to protect rope on the free hanging rappels.

Approach

From Devils Kitchen Picnic Area parking lot, either:
A) hike a short distance to the start of the wide, well-maintained and easy grade Serpents Trail or
B) scramble up the side canyon to intersect with the Serpents Trail higher up. Hike up the faint use-trail just behind and left of the ladies bathroom. There is one 5.5 move up a crack RUC. Send the best climber first and belay the others. Connect with the Serpents Trail.

Take the Serpents Trail to its end at a parking location with limited parking at Monument Rd.
Continue uphill up the next switchback to the right on Monument Rd. Walk the road for ~500ft until it is possible to walk the slickrock on the right and get off the shoulder for safety.

Head west around the head of Serpents Canyon. Follow the single power line northeast ~1200ft to the head of Adder Canyon.

Descent

Stay in the middle of the dry falls for the most impressive drops into deep alcoves.

  • R1: boulder, middle, 60 feet, free hang

39.03657, -108.64522

  • R2: tree, middle, 50 feet, free hang

39.03674. -108.64496

  • R3: small boulder- may need to convert to deadman/cairn, middle, 50 feet, free hang
  • R4: tree, middle-right, 200 feet if using webbing extended 10 feet, or 220 feet with retrievable

Low angle slab rappel 39.03748, -108.64311

  • R5: tree, left, 140 feet, short free hang at bottom
  • Friendly 10 foot down-climb followed by brief bush whacking
  • Optional water slide, 75 feet

Exit

Stay in the watercourse until you get to the bottom of the mostly dry waterslide. When you are nearly in someone's backyard, head right on the well-worn but intermittent trail back to Monument Road and then a 5 minute walk up the road.

Background

First known descent 10/29/2016 by Logan DeGrand, Erek Burek, Scott Bordon, and Wes.
